diff --git a/crates/codegen/xai-grok-pager/docs/user-guide/04-slash-commands.md b/crates/codegen/xai-grok-pager/docs/user-guide/04-slash-commands.md
index 4c78930..d33ee55 100644
--- a/crates/codegen/xai-grok-pager/docs/user-guide/04-slash-commands.md
+++ b/crates/codegen/xai-grok-pager/docs/user-guide/04-slash-commands.md
@@ -142,18 +142,22 @@ colon suffix or a second argument:
 Provider-prefixed IDs such as `openai-codex/gpt-5.5` explicitly select the
 provider. The suffix is parsed from the last colon only after trying the whole
 string as an exact model ID, so IDs that contain colons continue to work.
-Supported canonical levels are `none`, `minimal`, `low`, `medium`, `high`, and
-`xhigh` (subject to the selected model's offered levels).
+Supported canonical levels are `none`, `minimal`, `low`, `medium`, `high`,
+`xhigh`, and `max` (subject to the selected model's offered levels). `max` is
+a real level above `xhigh` on models that offer it (currently the Codex
+gpt-5.6 family); on other models it downgrades to `xhigh`, matching its old
+alias behavior.
 
 Aliases: `/m`
 
 ### `/effort <level>`
 
-Set reasoning effort on the **current** model without re-selecting it. Levels: `low`, `medium`, `high`, `xhigh`. Only works when the active model supports reasoning effort.
+Set reasoning effort on the **current** model without re-selecting it. Levels: `low`, `medium`, `high`, `xhigh` — plus `max` on models that offer it (e.g. Codex gpt-5.6; elsewhere `max` downgrades to `xhigh`). Only works when the active model supports reasoning effort.
 
 ```
 /effort high
 /effort low
+/effort max
 ```
 
 ### `/always-approve` and `/auto`
diff --git a/crates/codegen/xai-grok-pager/docs/user-guide/11-custom-models.md b/crates/codegen/xai-grok-pager/docs/user-guide/11-custom-models.md
